HEADWORD: Xylophagan
<hw>Xy*loph"a*gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Xylophagous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of
a tribe of beetles whose larvae bore or live in wood.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Any species of <gen>Xylophaga</gen>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Any
one of the <fam>Xylophagides</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
